sequentialTasks.description:
In a new or existing JS chunk (likely pr_split_06_verification.js or a new pr_split_06b_verify_shell.js if the file is already large), implement:

```javascript
function spawnShellSession(worktreeDir, mux, opts) {
    // 1. Detect shell: opts.shell || process.env.SHELL || '/bin/sh'
    // 2. Create CaptureSession: termmux.newCaptureSession(shell, [], { dir: worktreeDir, rows: opts.rows, cols: opts.cols })
    // 3. Start the session
    // 4. Save current mux child state (was Claude attached?)
    // 5. If Claude attached, detach
    // 6. Attach shell session to mux
    // 7. Call mux.switchTo() — BLOCKING passthrough
    // 8. On return: close shell session
    // 9. Re-attach Claude if was previously attached
    // 10. Call opts.onExit() callback
    // Returns: { exitCode, output }
}
```

This function orchestrates the full shell lifecycle using existing termmux primitives (newCaptureSession, attach, detach, switchTo). No Go-level changes required.

Expose as `prSplit.spawnShellSession` for TUI handler access.
